00:59:09.420 --> 00:59:12.380
do you have for
our leaders for how

00:59:12.380 --> 00:59:16.010
to listen, respond,
be with what's

00:59:16.010 --> 00:59:18.085
being asked of them right now?

00:59:18.085 --> 00:59:18.960
KRISTA TIPPETT: Yeah.

00:59:18.960 --> 00:59:19.560
You're right.

00:59:19.560 --> 00:59:21.480
I think, when you talk
about loaded questions,

00:59:21.480 --> 00:59:23.188
then they're not really
questions, right?

00:59:23.188 --> 00:59:27.720
They're arguments
presented as questions.

00:59:27.720 --> 00:59:29.940
That just feels like
a huge responsibility

00:59:29.940 --> 00:59:30.960
to answer that question.

00:59:35.350 --> 00:59:44.640
I do think that what the world
needs leaders in this sphere

00:59:44.640 --> 00:59:51.930
to be asking is,
how will we shape

00:59:51.930 --> 01:00:00.490
these technologies to human
purpose, to be good for us?

01:00:00.490 --> 01:00:04.290
And if I say, audaciously,
that these are the tools--

01:00:04.290 --> 01:00:06.570
you have created the tools to--

01:00:10.110 --> 01:00:14.420
whereby we could start to
think and act as a species--

01:00:14.420 --> 01:00:16.820
and we must, if we're
going to tackle something

01:00:16.820 --> 01:00:21.090
like climate change, just to
name one of our big challenges,

01:00:21.090 --> 01:00:23.390
but perhaps the one that
is the ultimate one.

01:00:26.290 --> 01:00:31.750
How can that-- like, I don't
want to say it as a problem--

01:00:31.750 --> 01:00:34.690
how to rise to that challenge--

01:00:34.690 --> 01:00:36.955
take that on as a
design question.

01:00:39.960 --> 01:00:44.290
Disrupt all the
compartmentalization.

01:00:44.290 --> 01:00:47.429
Disrupt all these
barriers and walls

01:00:47.429 --> 01:00:48.970
between all the
different disciplines

01:00:48.970 --> 01:00:51.490
we need to be
talking to each other

01:00:51.490 --> 01:00:55.004
to wrap our arms around some
of these big challenges.

01:00:55.004 --> 01:00:57.170
DANIELLE KRETTEK: I think,
I'd add to that as well--

01:00:57.170 --> 01:01:01.380
because I just
wholeheartedly agree--

01:01:01.380 --> 01:01:05.460
