01:01:22.770 --> 01:01:25.371
there are things about humanity
that will never change.

01:01:25.371 --> 01:01:27.120
There are the things
that are wired inside

01:01:27.120 --> 01:01:28.990
of us that will always be true.

01:01:28.990 --> 01:01:31.380
How do we think
as slow as we can

01:01:31.380 --> 01:01:33.600
to the things that never change?

01:01:33.600 --> 01:01:36.540
Because that's where the
real responses will come.

01:01:36.540 --> 01:01:38.670
The fast answers
are so challenging

01:01:38.670 --> 01:01:41.670
and loaded-- as loaded as the
questions and as dangerous

01:01:41.670 --> 01:01:43.050
for individuals too.

01:01:43.050 --> 01:01:45.557
There's just so much
going on in that moment.

01:01:45.557 --> 01:01:47.640
When, really, when we stop
and think about the way

01:01:47.640 --> 01:01:49.890
that we are, as
people, and the way

01:01:49.890 --> 01:01:51.690
that we are as people
together, and what

01:01:51.690 --> 01:01:53.880
it means to live in
a particular way,

01:01:53.880 --> 01:01:55.380
that we can all be
proud of and that

01:01:55.380 --> 01:01:57.810
feels like it is about
human flourishing

01:01:57.810 --> 01:02:01.980
and civility and the space
that includes all of us.

01:02:01.980 --> 01:02:03.240
Those are harder questions.

01:02:03.240 --> 01:02:04.579
Those are feeling questions.

01:02:04.579 --> 01:02:06.870
We're not all necessarily in
the practice of that, even

01:02:06.870 --> 01:02:07.980
personally.

01:02:07.980 --> 01:02:10.890
Just encouraging and having
those conversations here,

01:02:10.890 --> 01:02:14.310
making space for that, that's
the beginning of all of it.

01:02:14.310 --> 01:02:17.460
So I thank you for
doing your work

01:02:17.460 --> 01:02:19.160
and for asking the questions.

01:02:19.160 --> 01:02:24.660
KRISTA TIPPETT: Something else
I might say is, given that--

01:02:24.660 --> 01:02:27.900
I don't think anybody who
started any of these companies

01:02:27.900 --> 01:02:31.900
wanted to be changing human na--

01:02:31.900 --> 01:02:36.310
interwoven into people's bodies,
brains, and psyches, right?

01:02:36.310 --> 01:02:37.940
That's not what
anybody set out to do.

01:02:37.940 --> 01:02:39.064
But that's what's happened.

01:02:42.420 --> 01:02:48.750
A lot of the terrible reckonings
we're having now, even around

01:02:48.750 --> 01:02:51.690
things that we thought we'd
made great progress on socially,

01:02:51.690 --> 01:02:57.580
like racial dynamics
and gender dynamics--

01:02:57.580 --> 01:03:01.920
50 years ago, there were
beautiful movements,

01:03:01.920 --> 01:03:04.680
and a lot of laws changed.

01:03:04.680 --> 01:03:07.440
And we kind of came into
the 21st century thinking,

01:03:07.440 --> 01:03:08.470
we cracked this.

01:03:08.470 --> 01:03:11.250
We can keep getting better at
it, but we basically did this.

01:03:11.250 --> 01:03:13.530
And we hadn't.

01:03:13.530 --> 01:03:18.440
And one way I analyze
that is that we

01:03:18.440 --> 01:03:21.772
have this idea that,
if you know history,

01:03:21.772 --> 01:03:22.730
it won't repeat itself.

01:03:22.730 --> 01:03:25.400
But the truth is, actually, that
history always repeats itself

01:03:25.400 --> 01:03:28.110
until you know yourself.

01:03:28.110 --> 01:03:34.690
And we changed laws, but
we didn't change ourselves.

01:03:34.690 --> 01:03:37.750
And now, again, with
science as our companion,

01:03:37.750 --> 01:03:39.930
we learn about implicit bias.

01:03:39.930 --> 01:03:42.890
We learn how our
brains were hard wires.

01:03:42.890 --> 01:03:45.520
And we didn't know
how to effect that.

01:03:45.520 --> 01:03:49.140
The beautiful thing-- so it's
terrible to wake up to the fact

01:03:49.140 --> 01:03:52.297
that we were so much less
farther along than we thought.

01:03:52.297 --> 01:03:53.880
But the beautiful
thing is we actually

01:03:53.880 --> 01:03:57.450
now know we have knowledge
that can be a form of power.

01:03:57.450 --> 01:04:00.660
And you are working in a
sphere that is actively

01:04:00.660 --> 01:04:02.880
engaging our brains--

01:04:02.880 --> 01:04:06.180
actively involved in our
inner lives as well as

01:04:06.180 --> 01:04:08.530
our outer lives.

01:04:08.530 --> 01:04:12.330
So again, I would say, take
that as a creative challenge,

01:04:12.330 --> 01:04:15.600
a generative challenge.

01:04:15.600 --> 01:04:17.070
And it's uncomfortable, right?

01:04:17.070 --> 01:04:17.640
I know.

01:04:17.640 --> 01:04:18.930
It's not what anybody wanted.

01:04:18.930 --> 01:04:20.607
But there it is.

01:04:20.607 --> 01:04:23.190
DANIELLE KRETTEK: I'm going to
